Overview  Service   Command 

Service: zimbraMail
Namespace: "urn:zimbraMail"
GetMsgMetadata SOAP Command

Get message metadata

Authorization token required true
Admin Authorization token required false

GetMsgMetadataRequest

    <GetMsgMetadataRequest> ## GetMsgMetadataRequest
        <m ids="{ids}" /> ## IdsAttr
    </GetMsgMetadataRequest>

The following table describes elements and attributes you can define within a <GetMsgMetadataRequest> element:

XPath Required / Optional Description
/m Required (only 1) Messages selector
/m@ids Required (only 1) Type:String
IDs

The following table describes elements and attributes you can define within a <GetMsgMetadataResponse> element:

XPath Required / Optional Description
/chat Optional (0 or 1)
/chat@id Required (only 1) Type:String
Message ID
/chat@autoSendTime Optional (0 or 1) Type:Long
Auto send time
/chat@s Optional (0 or 1) Type:Long
Size in bytes
/chat@d Optional (0 or 1) Type:Long
Date Seconds since the epoch, from the date header in the message
/chat@l Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Folder ID
/chat@cid Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Converstation ID. only present if <m> is not enclosed within a <c> element
/chat@f Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Flags. (u)nread, (f)lagged, has (a)ttachment, (r)eplied, (s)ent by me, for(w)arded, calendar in(v)ite, (d)raft, IMAP-\Deleted (x), (n)otification sent, urgent (!), low-priority (?), priority (+)
/chat@t Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Tags - Comma separated list of integers. DEPRECATED - use "tn" instead
/chat@tn Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Comma separated list of tag names
/chat@rev Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Revision
/chat@md Optional (0 or 1) Type:Long
Date metadata changed
/chat@ms Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Change sequence
/chat/e Optional (0 or more) Email address information
/chat/e@a Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
the user@domain part of an email address
/chat/e@d Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Display name. If we have personal name, first word in "word1 word2" format, or last word in "word1, word2" format. If no personal name, take string before "@" in email-address.
/chat/e@p Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
The comment/name part of an address
/chat/e@t Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Address type.
{address-type} = (f)rom, (t)o, (c)c, (b)cc, (r)eply-to, (s)ender, read-receipt (n)otification, (rf) resent-from

Type is only sent when an individual message is returned. In the list of conversations, all the email addresseses returned for a conversation are a subset of the participants. In the list of messages in a converstation, the email addressses are the senders.

Note that "rf" addresses can only be returned on a message; when sending a message, "rf" is ignored
/chat/e@isGroup Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Set if the email address is a group
/chat/e@exp Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Flags whether can expand group members
1 (true) authed user can (has permission to) expand members in this group
0 (false) authed user does not have permission to expand group members
Note: Present only when {email-addr-is-group} is set.
/chat/su Optional (0 or 1) Type:{subject} (String)
Subject
/chat/fr Optional (0 or 1) Type:{fragment} (String)
First few bytes of the message (probably between 40 and 100 bytes)
/chat/inv Optional (0 or 1) Invite information
/chat/inv@type Required (only 1) Type:String
Invite type - appt|task
/chat/inv/tz Optional (0 or more) Timezones
/chat/inv/tz@id Required (only 1) Type:String
Timezone ID. If this is the only detail present then this should be an existing server-known timezone's ID Otherwise, it must be present, although it will be ignored by the server
/chat/inv/tz@stdoff Required (only 1) Type:Integer
Standard Time's offset in minutes from UTC; local = UTC + offset
/chat/inv/tz@dayoff Required (only 1) Type:Integer
Daylight Saving Time's offset in minutes from UTC; present only if DST is used
/chat/inv/tz@stdname Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Standard Time component's timezone name
/chat/inv/tz@dayname Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Daylight Saving Time component's timezone name
/chat/inv/tz/standard Optional (0 or 1) Time/rule for transitioning from daylight time to standard time. Either specify week/wkday combo, or mday.
/chat/inv/tz/standard@week Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Week number; 1=first, 2=second, 3=third, 4=fourth, -1=last
/chat/inv/tz/standard@wkday Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Day of week; 1=Sunday, 2=Monday, etc.
/chat/inv/tz/standard@mon Required (only 1) Type:Integer
Month; 1=January, 2=February, etc.
/chat/inv/tz/standard@mday Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Day of month (1..31)
/chat/inv/tz/standard@hour Required (only 1) Type:Integer
Transition hour (0..23)
/chat/inv/tz/standard@min Required (only 1) Type:Integer
Transition minute (0..59)
/chat/inv/tz/standard@sec Required (only 1) Type:Integer
Transition second; 0..59, usually 0
/chat/inv/tz/daylight Optional (0 or 1) Time/rule for transitioning from standard time to daylight time
See /chat/inv/tz/standard for more details.
/chat/inv/comp Optional (0 or 1) Invite components
/chat/inv/comp@method Required (only 1) Type:String
Method
/chat/inv/comp@compNum Required (only 1) Type:int
Component number of the invite
/chat/inv/comp@rsvp Required (only 1) Type:0|1
RSVP flag. Set if response requested, unset if no response requested
/chat/inv/comp@priority Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Priority (0 - 9; default = 0)
/chat/inv/comp@name Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
NAME
/chat/inv/comp@loc Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Location
/chat/inv/comp@percentComplete Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Percent complete for VTODO (0 - 100; default = 0)
/chat/inv/comp@completed Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
VTODO COMPLETED DATE-TIME in format yyyyMMddThhmmssZ
/chat/inv/comp@noBlob Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Set if invite has no blob data, i.e. all data is in db metadata
/chat/inv/comp@fba Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
The "actual" free-busy status of this invite (ie what the client should display). This is synthesized taking into account our Attendee's PartStat, the Opacity of the appointment, its Status, etc...
Valid values - F|B|T|U. i.e. Free, Busy (default), busy-Tentative, OutOfOffice (busy-unavailable)
/chat/inv/comp@fb Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
FreeBusy setting F|B|T|U
i.e. Free, Busy (default), busy-Tentative, OutOfOffice (busy-unavailable)
/chat/inv/comp@transp Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Transparency - O|T. i.e. Opaque or Transparent
/chat/inv/comp@isOrg Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Am I the organizer? [default 0 (false)]
/chat/inv/comp@x_uid Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
x_uid
/chat/inv/comp@uid Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
UID to use when creating appointment. Optional: client can request the UID to use
/chat/inv/comp@seq Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Sequence number (default = 0)
/chat/inv/comp@d Optional (0 or 1) Type:Long
Date - used for zdsync
/chat/inv/comp@calItemId Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Mail item ID of appointment
/chat/inv/comp@apptId Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Appointment ID (deprecated)
/chat/inv/comp@ciFolder Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Folder of appointment
/chat/inv/comp@status Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Status - TENT|CONF|CANC|NEED|COMP|INPR|WAITING|DEFERRED
i.e. TENTative, CONFirmed, CANCelled, COMPleted, INPRogress, WAITING, DEFERRED
where waiting and Deferred are custom values not found in the iCalendar spec.
/chat/inv/comp@class Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Class = PUB|PRI|CON. i.e. PUBlic (default), PRIvate, CONfidential
/chat/inv/comp@url Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
URL
/chat/inv/comp@ex Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Set if this is invite is an exception
/chat/inv/comp@ridZ Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Recurrence-id string in UTC timezone
/chat/inv/comp@allDay Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Set if is an all day appointment
/chat/inv/comp@draft Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Set if invite has changes that haven't been sent to attendees; for organizer only
/chat/inv/comp@neverSent Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Set if attendees were never notified of this invite; for organizer only
/chat/inv/comp@changes Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Comma-separated list of changed data in an updated invite.
Possible values are "subject", "location", "time" (start time, end time, or duration), and "recurrence".
/chat/inv/comp/category Optional (0 or more) Type:{categories} (String)
Categories - for iCalendar CATEGORY properties
/chat/inv/comp/comment Optional (0 or more) Type:{comments} (String)
Comments - for iCalendar COMMENT properties
/chat/inv/comp/contact Optional (0 or more) Type:{contacts} (String)
Contacts - for iCalendar CONTACT properties
/chat/inv/comp/geo Optional (0 or 1) for iCalendar GEO property
/chat/inv/comp/geo@lat Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Longitude (float value)
/chat/inv/comp/geo@lon Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Longitude (float value)
/chat/inv/comp/at Optional (0 or more) Attendees
/chat/inv/comp/at@a Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Email address (without "MAILTO:")
/chat/inv/comp/at@url Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
URL - has same value as {email-address}.
Maintained for backwards compatibility with ZCS 4.5
/chat/inv/comp/at@d Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Friendly name - "CN" in iCalendar
/chat/inv/comp/at@sentBy Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
iCalendar SENT-BY
/chat/inv/comp/at@dir Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
iCalendar DIR - Reference to a directory entry associated with the calendar user. the property.
/chat/inv/comp/at@lang Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
iCalendar LANGUAGE - As defined in RFC5646 * (e.g. "en-US")
/chat/inv/comp/at@cutype Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
iCalendar CUTYPE (Calendar user type)
/chat/inv/comp/at@role Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
iCalendar ROLE
/chat/inv/comp/at@ptst Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
iCalendar PTST (Participation status)
Valid values: NE|AC|TE|DE|DG|CO|IN|WE|DF
Meanings:
"NE"eds-action, "TE"ntative, "AC"cept, "DE"clined, "DG" (delegated), "CO"mpleted (todo), "IN"-process (todo), "WA"iting (custom value only for todo), "DF" (deferred; custom value only for todo)
/chat/inv/comp/at@rsvp Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
iCalendar RSVP
/chat/inv/comp/at@member Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
iCalendar MEMBER - The group or list membership of the calendar user
/chat/inv/comp/at@delTo Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
iCalendar DELEGATED-TO
/chat/inv/comp/at@delFrom Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
iCalendar DELEGATED-FROM
/chat/inv/comp/at/xparam Optional (0 or more) Non-standard parameters (XPARAMs)
/chat/inv/comp/at/xparam@name Required (only 1) Type:String
XPARAM Name
/chat/inv/comp/at/xparam@value Required (only 1) Type:String
XPARAM value
/chat/inv/comp/alarm Optional (0 or more) Alarm information
/chat/inv/comp/alarm@action Required (only 1) Type:String
Alarm action
Possible values:
DISPLAY|AUDIO|EMAIL|PROCEDURE|X_YAHOO_CALENDAR_ACTION_IM|X_YAHOO_CALENDAR_ACTION_MOBILE
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger Optional (0 or 1) Alarm trigger information
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/abs Optional (0 or 1) Absolute trigger information
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/abs@d Required (only 1) Type:String
Date in format : YYYYMMDDThhmmssZ
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel Optional (0 or 1) Relative trigger information
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel@neg Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Set if the duration is negative.
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel@w Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Weeks component of the duration
Special note: if WEEKS are specified, NO OTHER OFFSET MAY BE SPECIFIED (weeks must be alone, per RFC2445)
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel@d Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Days component of the duration
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel@h Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Hours component of the duration
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel@m Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Minutes component of the duration
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel@s Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Seconds component of the duration
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel@related Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Specifies whether the alarm is related to the start of end.
Valid values are : START|END
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel@count Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Alarm repeat count
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/repeat Optional (0 or 1) Alarm repeat information
See /chat/inv/comp/alarm/trigger/rel for more details.
/chat/inv/comp/alarm/desc Optional (0 or 1) Type:{description} (String)

TZID
/chat/inv/comp/recur/add/exclude/dates/dtval Optional (0 or more) Information on start date/time and end date/time or duration
/chat/inv/comp/recur/add/exclude/dates/dtval/s Optional (0 or 1) Start DATE-TIME
/chat/inv/comp/recur/add/exclude/dates/dtval/s@d Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Date and/or time. Format is : YYYYMMDD['T'HHMMSS[Z]]
where: 
     YYYY - 4 digit year
     MM   - 2 digit month
     DD   - 2 digit day
 Optionally:
     'T' the literal char "T" then 
     HH - 2 digit hour (00-23)
     MM - 2 digit minute (00-59)
     SS - 2 digit second (00-59)
     ...and finally an optional "Z" meaning that the time is UTC,
     otherwise the tz="TIMEZONE" param MUST be specified with the DATETIME
     e.g:
         20050612  June 12, 2005
         20050315T18302305Z  March 15, 2005 6:30:23.05 PM UTC
/chat/inv/comp/recur/add/exclude/dates/dtval/s@tz Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Java timezone identifier
/chat/inv/comp/recur/add/exclude/dates/dtval/s@u Optional (0 or 1) Type:Long
UTC time as milliseconds since the epoch. Set if non-all-day

/chat/inv/comp/recur/add/exclude/rule/bymonthday@modaylist Required (only 1) Type:String
Comma separated list of day numbers from either the start (positive) or the end (negative) of the month - format : [[+]|-]num[,...] where num between 1 to 31
e.g. modaylist="1,+2,-7"
means first day of the month, plus the 2nd day of the month, plus the 7th from last day of the month.
/chat/inv/comp/recur/add/exclude/rule/byyearday Optional (0 or 1) BYYEARDAY rule
/chat/inv/comp/recur/add/exclude/rule/byyearday@yrdaylist Required (only 1) Type:String
BYYEARDAY yearday list. Format : [[+]|-]num[,...]" where num is between 1 and 366
e.g. <byyearday yrdaylist="1,+2,-1"/> means January 1st, January 2nd, and December 31st.
/chat/inv/comp/recur/add/exclude/rule/byweekno Optional (0 or 1) BYWEEKNO rule

e.g. <byweekno wklist="1,+2,-1"/> means first week, 2nd week, and last week of the year.
